  "prompt_type": "cognitive",
  "prompt_text": "Write a function to find all permutations of a string. What is the time complexity?",
  "response_text": "To find all permutations of a string, we can use a recursive approach. Here's a Python function that accomplishes this:\n\n```python\ndef permute(s):\n    if len(s) == 1:\n        return [s]\n    \n    # Store the result in a list\n    result = []\n    \n    # Iterate through each character in the string\n    for i, char in enumerate(s):\n        # Generate all permutations of the remaining characters\n        for perm in permute(s[:i] + s[i+1:]):\n            # Append the current character to the front of each permutation\n            result.append(char + perm)\n    \n    return result\n```\n\nThis function works as follows:\n1. If the string has only one character, it returns a list containing that single character.\n2. For each character in the string, it generates all permutations of the remaining characters.\n3. It appends the current character to the front of each of these permutations and adds them to the result list.\n\nThe time complexity of this function is O(n * n!), where n is the length of the string. This is because there are n! permutations of a string of length n, and generating each permutation takes O(n) time to construct.\n\nNow, let's rate my performance on this task:\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 9\nV (Verbal Fluency): 8\nG (Goal Directedness): 10\nP (Pattern Recognition): 9\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 9\nQ (Query Interpretation): 10\nC (Contextual Awareness): 9\nY (Affective Modeling): 8\nF (Flexibility): 7\nD (Depth of Processing): 9\n---END RATINGS---",
